                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Regular and careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        Scribe: Dästa Gabra Māryām. Priest
                        Dästa Gabra Māryām from Lǝgat is mentioned as the scribe in the colophon. He
                        is the same scribe who wrote Mss. FBM-012 and UM-008.<date>20th
                           century</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለዓ፡ ዓ፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#16vb">16vb</locus>, 35vb, 50ra)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለዓ፡ ዓለ፡ አ፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ </expan> (e.g.,
                                 <locus target="#7va">7va</locus>, 22ra, 30ra, 75rb)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist, names of the
                           donor and other persons; groups of lines on the incipit page; incipit of
                           all sections; incipit or the initial word of subsections; the word salām
                           "salutation"; the word baʾǝnta "about" on fol. 62ra; elements of the
                           punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
